					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wishun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1204404); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1204404&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251320" alt="wishun" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1204404)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wishun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1204404); return false;" >wishun</a></span> <span class="odate time_1339516506 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Jun 2012 15:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1478061">
									

<p>So, when the Intruder changed that first battle, he created the University-verse. And now there is nothing he can do about it because any changes he makes just create another parrallel universe. So in this short snippet he has created 3 new universe, one where Jackson's assassin is caught by a mob, one where he is caught by Jackson's friends, and one where the pistols misfire. If he is spending all this effort to un-do the damage of just one change, shouldn't he be trying harder to minimize the propagtion of parallel realities he keeps spinning off?</p>
<p>Don't mind me, over-analyzing the quirks of time travel is sort of a hobby. It's a good story and I'm interested in seeing where it goes next.</p>

							</div>

								
